    Let <fr:tex>a\colon  X_\bullet \to  S</fr:tex> be an augmented simplicial topological space.
    For every sheaf <fr:tex>F</fr:tex> on <fr:tex>S</fr:tex>, we have a morphism
    <fr:tex
display="block">       \varphi \colon  F       \to  a_*a^*F     </fr:tex>
    from the adjunction <fr:tex>a^*\dashv  a_*</fr:tex>.
    This morphism derives to a morphism of functors from <fr:tex>\mathrm {D}^+(S)</fr:tex> to <fr:tex>\mathrm {D}^+(S)</fr:tex>, namely

    <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
